design.title: Dtail de conception
design.content:
Le design de la torche a t imagin pour inspirer le bonheur  tous ceux qui la contemplent.
Elle mesure 700 mm de long, ce qui reprsente l'altitude de PyeongChang, situe  700 m au-dessus du niveau de la mer. 
Moins potique mais trs historique : le dessous de la torche est une plaque ralise avec des barbels fondus de la DMZ.
design.content-en:
The torch was designed to inspire happiness in all those who lay eyes on it. It is 700mm in length, representing the altitude of PyeongChang, which is 700m above sea level.
Less poetic but of great historical significance: the bottom cap of the torch was made using melted-down barbed wire from the DMZ.

design.title: Dtail de conception
design.content:
La surface lisse et laiteuse rappelle la porcelaine blanche traditionnelle.
Les cinq branches formant le caractre  ?  figurent l'esprit sportif qui lie peuples, nations, religions, sexes et cultures. Et bien sr, les 5 continents unis par une passion commune pour les Jeux !
design.content-en: The smooth, milky white surface evokes traditional white porcelain. The five branches, which form the character "?", represent the spirit of sport that connects peoples, nations, religions, genders and cultures. And, of course, the five continents, united by a shared passion for the Games!

design.title: Dtail de conception
design.content:
La torche a t conue afin que la flamme continue  brler quelles que soient les conditions mto: vents forts ou abondantes chutes de neige. En soufflant en direction de la flamme, le vent cre un tunnel d'air apportant davantage d'oxygne. 
Le bas de la torche est galement pourvu d'une ouverture en forme de pentagone permettant  de l'eau de s'couler.
design.content-en: The torch was designed so that the flame would continue to burn in all weather conditions, from strong winds to heavy snowfall. When wind blew towards the flame, an air-tunnel was created, which provided more oxygen. There was also a pentagon-shaped hole at the bottom of the torch so that water could drain down.

doyouknow.title: Le saviez-vous ?
doyouknow.content:
Pour la premire fois au monde, des robots participent au relais de la flamme olympique.
Hubo, un humanode qui mesure 120 cm et pse 55 kg, a march environ 20 m avant de trouer un mur et de transmettre la torche olympique a FX-2. Mesurant lui 2,5 m et pesant 280 kg, il peut porter un adulte de 70 kg.
doyouknow.content-en: For the first time ever, robots took part in the Olympic Torch Relay. Hubo, a 120cm-tall humanoid weighing 55kg, walked for about 20m before drilling a hole in a wall and passing the Olympic torch to FX-2. This second robot torchbearer, 2.5m tall and weighing 280kg, is capable of carrying a 70kg adult.

relay.content-en: On 12 March 2020, the flame was lit in Olympia against the backdrop of the coronavirus pandemic. The following day, the Relay was suspended during the Greek leg to avoid exposing the population to the risk of infection. Nevertheless, the torch was still handed over to the Games Organising Committee on 19 March at the Panathenaic Stadium, albeit without spectators. On 20 March, the flame arrived in Japan. In a gesture of solidarity with the regions most severely affected by the earthquake and tsunami of 2011, the flame went on display in the prefectures of Iwate, Miyagi and Fukushima. On 24 March, due to the coronavirus pandemic, the Games were postponed to 2021, and the Relay was also postponed. The Olympic flame remained lit in the Tokyo Olympic Museum during this intervening period.
relay.title: Tokyo 2020
relay.content:
Le 12 mars 2020, la flamme est allume  Olympie dans un contexte de vague pandmique de coronavirus. Le jour suivant, le relais est interrompu sur sol grec afin de ne pas exposer les populations au risque de contagion. Nanmoins, la crmonie de remise de la flamme au comit dorganisation des Jeux a bien lieu le 19 mars au Stade panathnaque, mais sans public.
Le 20 mars, la flamme atterrit au Japon. En signe de solidarit avec les rgions durement touches par le sisme de 2011, la flamme est expose dans les prfectures dIwate, Miyagi et Fukushima. Le 24 mars, en raison de la pandmie de coronavirus, les Jeux sont reports en 2021. Par consquent, le relais subit le mme sort. Durant cette priode, la flamme olympique reste allume dans le Muse Olympique de Tokyo.

relay.content-en: With the Olympic Torch Relay visiting a range of municipalities across the country, nearly 98 per cent of the Japanese population lived less than an hour away by road or train from one of the relay legs.
relay.title: Transport
relay.content: Avec les relais organiss dans les diffrentes municipalits, prs de 98 % de la population du Japon se trouvait  moins dune heure de route ou de train du passage du relais de la flamme olympique.

relay.content-en: The Tokyo 2020 Olympic Torch Relay resumed on 25 March 2021. Over 121 days, the flame travelled through all 47 Japanese prefectures, showcasing a host of cultural attractions, iconic locations and historical sites. The coronavirus pandemic meant that no spectators were allowed to attend the Relay or the Games, but the Relay still came to its traditional conclusion, with tennis player Naomi OSAKA lighting the Olympic cauldron at the Opening Ceremony on 23 July.
relay.title: Itinraire de la flame
relay.content: Le relais de la flamme olympique de Tokyo 2020 a repris son priple le 25 mars 2021. En 121 jours, la flamme a travers les 47 prfectures du Japon en mettant en lumire de nombreuses attractions culturelles, des lieux emblmatiques et des sites historiques. Si le rebond de la pandmie de coronavirus lors de larrive de la flamme  Tokyo oblige les organisateurs dinterdire les spectateurs lors du relais et la tenue des Jeux, cela nempche pas la  joueuse de tennis Naomi OSAKA dallumer la vasque lors de la crmonie douverture le 23 juillet.

design.content-en:
The torch takes its inspiration from the sakura cherry blossom, a symbolic tree in Japan. It flares out at the top to form five petals from which the flame emerges and which, seen from above, recall the shape of a cherry blossom flower. 

The torch features a two-combustion mechanism that produces a high-calorific blue flame and a flameless catalytic reaction. This ensures that the flame stays alight and has a reddish colour.
design.title: Dtail de conception
design.content:
La torche tire son inspiration du cerisier sakura, un arbre emblmatique au Japon. Elle svase ainsi dans sa partie haute en cinq ptales do merge la flamme et qui, vus de dessus, rappellent la forme dune fleur de cerisier.
Elle possde un systme  double combustion qui produit une flamme bleue  forte combustion ainsi quune combustion sans flamme. Ceci afin de garantir la permanence de la flamme tout en lui apportant une teinte tirant sur le rouge.

design.content-en: The pink colour of the torch is also a reference to the sakura, and the central upper part features the Tokyo 2020 Olympic emblem. Thirty per cent of the torch is made from recycled aluminium, originally used for temporary housing built in the wake of the earthquake and tsunami that struck eastern Japan in 2011.

doyouknow.content-en: Each year, the people of Japan celebrate hanami, the cherry blossom festival, which heralds the start of spring. In parks, among the trees, families and friends gather to admire this symbol of ephemeral beauty and enjoy picnics. The arrival of the flame in Japan was timed to coincide with this season, which is much loved by the population.

relay.title: Beijing 2022
relay.content: Le 18 octobre 2021, en raison des restrictions lies  la pandmie de coronavirus, seuls quelques relayeurs portent la flamme  Olympie  la suite de son allumage. Elle est ensuite emmene  Athnes o, le lendemain, elle est remise aux reprsentants du comit dorganisation de Beijing 2022 au Stade panathnaque. Le 20 octobre, la flamme arrive en Chine. Le programme comprend la prsentation de la flamme dans diffrents sites et rgions du pays, puis un relais plus traditionnel pendant les trois jours prcdant la crmonie douverture.
relay.content-en: On 18 October 2021, due to coronavirus restrictions, only a limited number of torchbearers carried the flame in Olympia following its lighting. It was then taken to Athens where, the following day, it was handed over to representatives from the Beijing 2022 Organising Committee at the Panathenaic Stadium. On 20 October, the flame arrived in China. It was then displayed at various sites in various regions around the country, with a more traditional relay taking place in the three days before the Opening Ceremony.

relay.title: Transport
relay.content: Environ 1 200 relayeurs tranportent la torche du 02 au 04 fvrier 2022. Dans le Stade national, les derniers relayeurs de la flamme olympique sont la skieuse de fond YILAMUJIANG Dinigeer et le skieur de combin nordique ZHAO Jiawen.
relay.content-en: Around 1,200 torchbearers carried the torch between 2 and 4 February 2022. In the National Stadium, the final torchbearers were cross-country skier YILAMUJIANG Dinigeer and Nordic combined athlete ZHAO Jiawen.

relay.title: Itinraire de la flame
relay.content: Sant-Joie-nergie  est le slogan du relais. Il dbute le 02 fvrier par une crmonie au Parc forestier olympique de Pkin, en prsence de plus de 300 athltes, tudiants et bnvoles. Jusqu'au 04 fvrier, la flamme se rend dans les zones de comptition de Beijing, Zhangjiakou et Yanqing.
relay.content-en: Health-Joy-Energy was the slogan for the Relay, which began on 2 February with a ceremony at the Beijing Olympic Forest Park, with more than 300 athletes, students and volunteers in attendance. The flame then visited the competition zones in Beijing, Zhangjiakou and Yanqing until 4 February.

design.title: Dtail de conception
design.content: Le design de la torche associe lesthtisme et la culture traditionnelle chinoise  la technologie. Sa forme en spirale fait penser  deux rubans qui flottent et se chevauchent. Le premier ruban, de couleur rouge, reprsente des flammes montantes. Le second, argent, voque la glace. La poigne porte des motifs de flocons de neige tandis que la partie haute arbore lemblme de Beijing 2022.
design.content-en: The torch design combines traditional Chinese culture and aesthetics with technology. The upward spiral shape resembles two overlapping, fluttering ribbons. The inner red ribbon evokes rising flames, while the outer silver ribbon is reminiscent of ice. Snowflake patterns can also be seen on the handle, while the upper section of the torch features the Beijing 2022 emblem.
